text.__SUMMARY__: Conus freitasi is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae, the cone snails, cone shells or cones.These snails are predatory and venomous. They are capable of "stinging" humans.
text.Description: The length of the shell varies between 10.8 mm and 15.9 mm.
text.Distribution: This marine species of cone snail occurs off the Cape Verdes.
text.External links: Tenorio M.J., Afonso C.M.L., Rolán E., Pires S., Vasconcelos P., Abalde S. & Zardoya R. (2017). DNA sequences disclose a new species of Africonus cone snail from São Vicente (Gastropoda: Conidae). Zoologia Caboverdiana. 6(2): 32-41
